BNP’s Prot to Get EU1.67M 2010 Bonus, Tribune Says

-- B y   D a v i d   W h i t e h o u s e
-- 
2011-03-22T06:38:00Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-03-22/bnp-s-prot-to-get-eu1-67m-2010-bonus-tribune-says-correct-.html
(Corrects currency conversion in first paragraph.)  BNP Paribas (BNP)  SA Chief Executive
Officer Baudouin Prot has been given a bonus of 1.67 million
euros ($2.38 million) for the 2010 financial year, daily La
Tribune reported, citing the bank.  Sixty percent of the amount will be deferred until the
period from 2012 to 2014, La Tribune said. Prot’s total
compensation for 2010 is 2.7 million euros, according to the
newspaper.  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
David Whitehouse at 
 dwhitehouse1@bloomberg.net  